<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I thought I saw it on this board.  When you are a cleric with 4 other clerics doing the cheal rotation - can you setup a multiple casting hotkey?<P>I saw something like<P>/sit off<BR>/cast 3, /shout CHEAL ON %T<BR>/pause 125, /cast 3<P>something like that...  can someone help me?<P><P>------------------<BR>Hugs,<BR>Torriana <BR>60th Cleric<BR>Brell Serillis Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109127" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kegwell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">a pause  of 10 = 1 second, long pauses will kill your raid if a fizzle or a need for a heal on others arises. The best hotkey I have found to use is this..<BR>/cast ___ (slot CH is in)<BR>/1 (or /ooc or whatever chat you use) CH on %T (add your number in the rotation here)<BR>/pause 5 ( a half second pause)<BR>/cast ___(slot CH is in)<BR> If you DO fizzle, you will still cast the second time, if you dont fizzle, you get a dumb message that you can't use the ability, but your heal goes as planned. I leave the middle line open and stick a /say CH on %T or some other chat communication method there. Hope it helps, but I think trying to program pauses for 3 other clerics CH is never going to work.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ShelseaDruid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What I was wondering is there a way to set it up with the pause timer set for the number of clerics..<P>/sit off<BR>/cast 3, /shout CHEAL ON %T - CLERIC# you are next<BR>/pause 500 (125 per cleric - 4 clerics)<BR>/cast 3, /shout CHEAL ON %T - CLERIC# you are next<P>Something that would account for all the clerics casting...<P><P>------------------<BR>Hugs,<BR>Torriana <BR>60th Cleric<BR>Brell Serillis Server<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=109127" TARGET=_blank>Profile</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kegwell</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Um sounds good on paper, but what do you do when a cleric dies? or goes oom? what about medding while others are healing, theres some 20 minute battles out there..What about when the MT's defensive goes and you have to speed heal? Most slowable mobs require different rates of healing, one for unslowed, one for slowed and a third for slowed, with no discipline up, and to further complicate the issue, not all tanks are going to need the same frequency of heals. Overall, making a macro this comprehensive will remove all error, on YOUR part, but what about when a cleric fubars and forgets his number? or just plain is late? BOTS are far to common these days, and basically, this is a BOT macro, true clerics think and do way more than a BOT could ever do.<P>------------------<BR>Kegwell Soulsavior<BR>High Priest of Brell<BR>Shards of Avalon<BR>Xegony (the poor unwanted stepchild of servers)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Viscera</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, what the dorf said.<P>------------------<BR>Viscera Galen<BR>L60 High Priest of Brell<BR><A HREF="http://www.darktemplarsguild.co.uk" TARGET=_blank>Dark Templars</A><BR>Xegony<p>[This message has been edited by Viscera (edited 05-03-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Qamen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Every cleric in CH order need undertake which cleric u will follow when some CH down. eg. AA CH first then BB CH then CC CH, if BB down CC need follow AA automatic to cast CH.... that no need to ask !!<P>Btw don't 100% trust the /pause command, sometime when u are lag, espically the mob can AE DD, your /pause command will delay (I set my /pause 30 but I saw it delay up to 6 sec !!). Sometimes I will set faster a bit (eg CH order need /pause 30, I will set /pause 25 or 20, depend on lag or not) So if I do CH wave, I must self test my CH command to prevent delay order.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hurk</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">what we use for vindi:<P>/cast 3<BR>/gu (2) Castion Complete Heal on <<< %t >>> CLERIC you are next!<P>the (2)  is my place in the rotation... that way the backup can see who/what is going on.<P>I also have a second key that is:<P>/gu TARGET OOR OR OOM FILL IN FILL IN!<P>and<P>/gu (2) I AM BACK IN ROTATION</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">AeolwindStormrunner</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't use the /cast command, its too laggy in some fights and you can go way off the count.  Just click hotkey, then CH wait 10 secs, sit back down.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kaysha Soulsinger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Also note that when you have such a huge pause in your hotkey, your hotkey will still be considered "active" (it's still "running"), and hence you cannot use any other hotkey in the mean time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aariis_Stasis_Prexus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">CH rotations are easy, simply have 3- 4 clerics with good mana pool / connection for rotation.<P>My key usually looks like :<P>/1 (raid channel) CH on [%t] INC<BR>/cast # (spell icon number)<BR>/cast # (this is incase of fizzle)<BR>/pause 30 (usually 30 but adjust for situation)<BR>/1 (next cleric name) Your up!<P>As for a CH rotation cleric going oom or getting aggored and dying, have other clerics (non rotation) and druids and shammys to assist heal between the CH's, using Divine light or Natures touch, this keeps the rotation running smoothly and helps for tank transitions etc and always have a mage summoning V.20 mod rods for the CH clerics  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ajax34i</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aariis got it right, the idea is to watch for when the cleric before you says GO, cast your CH, and then tell the next cleric to GO after like 3 seconds.  That's what the /pause is there for.  The /pause command can cause too many problems (sputters, tanks running out of range, dead clerics in the chain), so it's not recommended that you use it to pile 15 CH's on one button.<P>Also, I think you can't have multiple commands per line, so /cast and /shout are incompatible, as far as I know.<P>So,<P>/cast 3<BR>/g CH on %T<BR>/pause 27<BR>/g Next Cleric GO<P>is the basic setup. <P>During the fight you'll be watching for that special person who goes before you to say "Next Cleric GO" at which point you hit the button.  When your heal hits, you check your range to the tank and the mob, check your mana, and sit if needed.  Then you wait again.<P>It gets tricky when things go out of sync, so you have to have a rule that if multiple people get out of order because of emergencies, the FIRST cleric casts out of turn and everyone follows him/her again.  <P>Otherwise everyone will look at that MT's bar, feel the need to CH, and you'll end up with 4 clerics telling each other to GO at the same time.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Morrun</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I actually did my first ever CH rotation this weekend (so sue me, I'm a casual player, level 60 or no  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> ).  4 clerics & 4 or 5 groups, on Dracoliche.  (hits for 600, taps, 80K hps).  Not that uber but a good place to start, I thought.<P>I went for the minimalist approach:<P>/stand<BR>/cast 1<BR>/6 Complete Heal %t, cleric_02 next!<BR>/cast 1<P>6 being the rotation-only chat channel I was used, obviously adjust to suit. Note I didn't specify an interval in the macro, the 4 of us agreed on that beforehand.<P>Yes, it means we had to remember the interval, so more work on our part, but that turned out to be a good thing - we started with a 4 second interval, but when we realised the MT wasn't going below 60% health, we backed off to an 8 second interval.  Saved us in the end, since we had enough mana to keep going till Draco died.  Worked pretty well, given that none of us had done a rotation before  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>A bit rambling, but the moral of the story is: don't try and do too much with macros.  The important thing is that the clerics in the rotation know what they're doing.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Morrun Catspaw<BR>High Priest of Bristlebane<BR>Albion - Death Before Dishonour!<BR>Cazic-Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cilene</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just a few things to say,<P>1. Never use the /pause comand, never works, trust me, unless u have uber comp n uber con.<BR>2. my ch macro looks like this<P>/cast 1<BR>/1 CH on %T next is 2<BR>/cast 1<P>all clerics in guild have 6 macroes set up where eatch one is a different #. at the beginning of raid, lead cleric gives everyone a #, n u pick ur macro accordingly. this also makes it very easy iff a cleric goes LD/oom/dies etc. the other cleric just picks the accourding macro n wiola ch chain keeps going <P>3. dont use /pause  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">ajax34i</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Some people use pause, some people don't.  Sometimes I use it, sometimes I don't.  I kind of got a feel for what it can do, cause I did have it mess me up really bad during a raid.<P>It's a handle with care command.<P>Never ride motorcycles!  Never pilot airplanes!  Never skydive!  Never bungee-jump!  Same thing.<P>Average human reaction time is 0.8 seconds.  Counting seconds without a timer in front of you...  20% wrong.  Distractions during fight can increase that.  All in all you could end up with a + or - 2 seconds delay in there, and sometimes that's alot.<P>Plus, if you've got a stranger cleric in your rotation, will you trust him or her with your MT's health?  It's easier to trust that someone's gonna hit a button when they see a prompt than it is to trust that someone will make the right call and heal your tank on time.<P>And, a million things could go wrong during a fight, and a messed up /pause sequence is only one of them.  Never heard anyone say "Man we tried this with /pause and we wiped, and then I told everyone to remove their /pauses and we won easy!"<P>Main Cleric says: "Set up a pause macro.  Use delay 27."<BR>Cleric 2 says: "Ok."<BR>Cleric 3 says: "Done."<BR>You say:  "No.  I don't like /pause and I'm not gonna use it."<P>Anyway, your call.<P><BR>[This message has been edited by ajax34i (edited 05-14-2002).]<p>[This message has been edited by ajax34i (edited 05-14-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cilene</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ok well we failed 3 times in a row using the /pause comand in my old guild on vindi. a friendly cleric from another guild was helping us n said how they did it, we removed the /pause more poeple left the raid, but we managed him.<BR>also with the pause comand people get lulled into a false sence of security, well i did</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kyrsten Soulshyne</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Coming from a Guild that raids alot, I can tell you all of our clerics hate the /pause.  It causes lag for us, and is just another way for your hotkeys to go wacky.<P>However, as far as CH chains go, In end game encounters its ALL about MT aggro.  Your CH chain is NO good if your healing a MT that has no aggro, and will lead to cleric deaths when your clerics get more aggro than that tank from CH's.  <P>If you haven't learned how to assist heal, do so.  Myself and other lead clerics have keys set up for this and call aggro.  YES in a perfect world it is the original MT, but the switching of tanks is the key to your raid force improving, and being able to accomplish more.<P><BR>------------------<BR><B>Kyrsten Soulshyne</B><BR><I> Sugar, Spice...and Everything Nice!</I><BR>High Priestess Of <A HREF="http://www.eqdestiny.com" TARGET=_blank>DESTINY</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=172797" TARGET=_blank>Kyrsten's Profile</A><p>[This message has been edited by Kyrsten Soulshyne (edited 05-14-2002).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">All healers in a "heal" channel.<P>/cast # (complete heal)<BR>/1 CH on TARGET<BR>/g CH on TARGET<P>I don't like to add the line "Cleric_03 GO!".  Set up your rotation ahead of time and have a back-up plan.  When you play with the same people all the time, you develop a routine that works for you.<P>My two cents anyway.<P>------------------<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34282" TARGET=_blank><B>Saela Vee</B></A><BR>High Priestess of <A HREF="http://pub78.ezboard.com/bthe